Dex Entry: Hatched from a green egg. These birds seek balance in the world.
Now a juvenile, the bird flies great horizons in the name of Guthix.
Known as a bird symbolizing harmony and balance. If it shows up, all is well.
Hatched from a red egg. These birds align with Zamorak.
Birds who flies over battlefields.They are known for enjoying chaos.
During the Third Age these hawks were used by falconers under Zamorak.
Hatched from a blue egg. They possess great wisdom from birth.
With age these birds gain evermore wisdom of law and order.
A herald of Saradomin. These owls align themselves to wise individuals who respects law and order above all else.
Newly hatched from an egg, these birds will one day be killed for feathers by adventurers.
Gielinor's finest creature and in great abundance. Their feathers make excellent arrows.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
While it is unclear how it is connected to the evil chicken. They do share a dreadfull magic attack.
This chicken adapted to underwater life after its home was sunken to the bottom of the oceas.
While seemingly unusable due to not laying eggs, they are great for getting up early.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Strictly found inside the kharazi jungle, their meat is used in the renowned "oomlie wrap".
A coward went inside draynor manor as a dare. Now his shape reflects his spirit.
Chickens who died, but became reanimated. They mainly hail fromMorytania.
It is unclear wether it is a lizard or a chicken. Nor what came first, the egg or the lizard.
With a beak mightier than any others, it faces any opponents on land or sea. One of the homunculus's greatest creations.
Pretentious and arrogant. It flexes its muscles and howls in the glory of itself and its creator.
A chicken known to eat its fellow chickens. Bad to the bone. It attacks adventurers on sight.
Unsteady on their feet, they never stray too far from their herd.
While they produce milk, most adventurers prefer their hide to make clothes.
Angry and impatient, these monsters do not like fashionable people in red.
An undead bovine who has lost its skin. They are great companions for teenage witches.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A cow who died in the ghastly lands of Morytania. Do not drink it's milk.
An experiment crossing the purity of a unicorn, with the shape of a cow. It's purity it still in question.
One of the weakest water creatures there is. Very envious of shrimps.
Often one of the first things fished by adventurers, shrimp never stay alone.
Praised by some as the best food in the free world. They are mostly found by the Karamja docks.
While very small, they are sometimes capable of killing kittens.
Too big for any cat to hunt. These rats lurk about in the wild in search of food.
The experiment of a witch. They fling ogleroots as their weapons.
A rat who lurks in the brine of the sea. They hold on to brine sabres.
A rat that has become white and with red eyes. They can not stop themselves from feasting on cheese.
Demonic rats, they are MALICIOUSLY CRUEL to anyone and TOTALLY EVIL.
Bigger than before, they are now capable of UNRELENTING MALICIOUSNESS.
A being so BRUTALLY ANTAGONISTIC it could not pass the custom. So it entered a coconut.
Rats adapting to the life in the dungeon. Their scars are from many battles with other rats.
The crypts of morytania warped these small rats, hardening their skills and aggresion.
Despite living in a crypt, this rat is beyond fat. All rats used to look more like this before.
A rat warped by a necromancer. Opening its mind to psychic powers, but losing the sanity.
Arisen from death, they serve as guards to Melzar the Mad.
A rat so deadly it could kill kittens with a single strike. They are known to form rat courts.
A king rat who lived to become a giant. Its hedonism and cruelty grew correspondingly.
Formed by the anger of Tolna, shaped to a rat. It knows only anger.
Iban, son of zamorak blessed these beings. Making them stronger than regular rats.
Woolless and unready for the world. The lamb only hopes to baa with its parents.
The favoured race of Guthix. Mostly sheared illegally by adventurers.
Not as easily sheared as sheep, these monsters enjoy to strike back at unprepared adventurers.
When a pirate accidentally said he wanted a 'pirate sheep' his crewmates gave him this. It was accepted into the crew.
A small and otherwise weak fish. But rich in nutrients and purines.
Not to be confused with red herrings from Sinclair Mansion. These fish live their entire lives in water.
Capable of crossing great lengths of water to mate, these fish can swim an entire day without rest.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Sporting a sword-like nose, these fish are very territorial over their turf.
When it is time to mate, these fish will climb the baxtorian falls, avoiding the whirlpools, to find a mate.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Its nose is long for territorial fights, as well as a handy tool for examining areas.
Their sail allows them to travel at far greater speed than swordfish, making them exceptional hunters.
The beast of the sea, it has been known to drown even the biggest ships and seasoned fishermen on the smallest of whims.
Often dropped on the ground by adventurers. These fish often feel lonely and alone.
A fish sporting a great number of teeth that can be regrown. Adventurers like to eat these in large numbers cooked.
A shark only found in the middle of the sea. They sometimes get caught in the fishing trawler, but most expeditions end up a wreck.
The most dangerous of all sharks, these fish will lash out and bite anything they find or deem edible.
During the reign of Captain Rabid Jack. A man was filled to the brim with mackerels as punishment.
Despite it's name, it is not a cat. But rather a fish. The whiskers threw marine biologists off.
It is unknown where these shark hail from. Some theorise they can only live inside lava.
A vital ingredient for fish oil, hailing from Waiko.
These fish are apparently distantly related to the mackerel, despite their uppity name.
A rare fish from the arc. It scours the reef hiding from predators and looking for food.
Despite its ferocious look, it is actully not a dangereous shark to humans and prefer to hunt small fish.
A fish that often gets the blame for children becoming angry or aggressive to others. It is unknown why.
As it shines in every colour conceivable, it was almost fished to extinction at one point.
A rare shark with a seemingly kind grin on its face. They are mostly seen in aquariums.
It is so rare and golden that it is sometimes hung up on the walls of houses. A rare prize for fishermen.
Since it is only found in the desert. It hides along the ocean floor camouflaged.
A rare fish that feeds on slimy eels. They can be crushed and used as bleach to decolour clothes.
A fish that only lives in the caves of the Dorgeshuun. Its taste is said to be very unique.
A fish so long it could be used as a belt. Apparently this is how it got it's name.
A deep sea fish usually only found through fishing trawlers. They taste delicious but are hard to come by.
A fish that is hard to catch, only catchable in Karamja. It is very poisonous.
An octopus whose method of being caught was a mystery to mostly anyone but the Tai Bwo Wannai. Nowadays everyone knows about it.
A carp that could single- handedly win someone a fishing contest. But it's tricky to bait it.
A fish known for its green colour. Only about half the pike fished by adventurers actually get cooked.
Only found in the Piscatoris fishing colony, they are sought after by sea trolls who fight humans for the land.
A monkfish so rare, that it's hardly eaten. Most find their way to aquariums in houses.
A fish that captivates its prey with a shining light. As they adore the light, it bites and swallows them whole.
Unable to live beyond their fish bowl container. They become quite discontent with their limited life.
A fish who wanted to see more than the ocean... But ironically needed to see the world through the ocean.
Living its entire life in underground water, it is unknown if they can even see in light.
Hard as a rock. Even harder to bite. These fish are tasty treats to most adventurers.
An eel whose only defensive strategy is to be so slimy it can slip out of any situation.
It prefers the water in caves. It had peace and solitude until the dorgeshuun realized their existence.
An eel that used to be worshipped in the past for its spiritual powers. Nowadays they are eaten like any other eel.
This fish can only survive in lava and requires special methods to be caught. One is needed to enter the heroes guild.
An eel once feared as an eel from Infernus, dimension of demons. No one knows or care for that since it tastes delicious these days.
These small things serve no real purpose to farmer but to grow into mud wrestlers.
Rumours has it that pigs have a purpose beyond merely mud wrestling. But the farmer who spread the rumour refused to tell.
A cute little pupper that would die for you. Whenever you leave home, it will stay by your door until you come back.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
In ancient times, these were used for hunting and detective work.
Used to guard sheep. These dogs will bark at anyone out of line, or run them down a cliff.
It is unknown how many spots a dalmation can truly have. The only thing we know is that some are brown and without any.
Known for their excellent speed, people use them for gambling in races.
Ready to fight at any moment. These dogs often get breathing problems.
Genetically engineered to emotionally love everyone. Loves head pats too.
Dogs that faithfully serve their queen, as long as they get lots of treats in the process.
A dog warped by Tarn in order to find the salve stone, he never succeeded.
A mangy mutt who wanders the street, looking for the occasional bone and adventurers to follow.
A skeletal hellhound who served as the lord of death, Harold's faithful companion.
When a puppy accidentally fell to the infernal dimension, it comes back as a hellpuppy.
A shakroth-type demon from infernus. They bite really hard if not fed.
Known for its 3 heads, it's unknown if the heads act as one or if they retain individual personalities.
Small and curious about the world. A kitten will do anything to play with a ball of wool.
Known for their rat hunting prowess, they have become a mainstay in Gielinor.
Since it has now grown to full size, it has become too lazy to actively hunt rats. The cat simply can not find the energy.
When a wily cat does not exercise it becomes a lazy cat. Out of shape and out of motivation. Just like its owner.
A cat trained to peak condition. Ready to strike at any rat it sees. They would fight a giant rat if allowed to.
Cat made purple by the powers of a sweet-tooth witch. It is unknown if there is more to it beyond the colour.
When a cat eats too many hell rats, they become a hellcat. Infused by the hell rats infernal energy.
Letters connect people, and cats connect cat lovers. The postcat is an epitome of them both.
Sent as an omen to warn the adventurer of a terrible, terrible future. A sunken future. It also removes special effect on command.
The reincarnation of Odysseus, the mighty panther who died in a battle versus the dragonkin. Really likes Fish.
An evil tyrant of whom most who have seen rarely survive. He takes slaves in to put them trough cruel services like uncooking fish.
Known as the best companion an adventurer could ever have. They will fetch any stick thrown.
The different forms of strykewyrms are well adapted and dangerous.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
While small, these arachnids pack a real punch if an adventurer gets stung.
Known to many as a king scorpion, these scorpions are far bigger than most adventurers.
Has a curious eye for everything. Many adventurers have gone mad from their stares.
Some say they watch adventurers and their every action to learn. Some theorize they gaze into their soul.
Made by a Gorajo, it lurks the Polymore Dungeon for food.
With its petrifying gaze, anyone who challenges it without a mirror will be left a garden ornament.
Small and harmless, it will one day grow big enough to destroy any gardeners dream.
A pest to Gardener Wyson. This mole destroys the Falador garden from below.
Happily jumping around without a care in the world. They often forget where they bury their nuts.
Hatched from a black egg. They rarely leave their nest on purpose.
Known to pick up anything shiny. If you find a birds nest with a ring in it, it most likely belonged to a raven.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
It picks up shiny objects from everywhere. But is most known by summoners for its horrible cockney accent.
Capable of running great lengths. All barbers in Mishtalin uses them as energy.
While usually passive, if provoked, they will put their all into exploding as a last resort.
A chinchompa with a golden coloration. They sell for a wealthy prize but do not explode.
Rarely leaving its nest before they can fly, they survive on scraps given by their parents.
Preying mostly on carcasses, they are important to the ecosystem as they remove diseased bodies from the world.
Young and immature, they mature fast as they learn of their oppressors.
Secret agents of the K.G.P on an undercover mission. Easily bribed by fish and cowbells.
Used to be a real parrot but they are no more, its gone, and it longs for the fjords.
With a great sense of smell, they are able to find anything from truffles to secret trapdoors.
A creature created by the magic of the tooth fairy. They turn rotten if they eat chocolate.
Created by rune crafting wizards, this automation is easily influenced by runic energy.
Given to winners of the golden gnome awards. Most being for pity or lack of competition.
A tinsel snake celebrating christmas. They refuse to curl around a tree.
Using echolocation they find their prey. They usually don't come out during the day.
One of the biggest bats there are. They have recently been hunted to make magic armour.
A bat warped by unknown energy. They have become aggressive; but not necessarily that strong.
Found in Mos Le'Harmless. These bats have lost all colour in their bodies.
Mostly used as court evidence, these bats are perfectly sheltered from sunlight.
Despite their vampyric cousins, these bats love fruit among all things. Especially papaya.
Whenever it clings to it's enemies, it will not let go until it is full of blood.
Known as a fire imp, these are the weakest demons that exist and love to play tricks on adventurers.
A Byzroth demon. Once slaves in their home realm. Now they fight for the god of chaos.
An Alyaroth demon. Once used as slaves to the Chthonians, they now spread their wings for Zamorak.
One of the strongest demons summoned by Bilrach for his lord. Zamorak used them as generals in his army.
A demon posessing the power of fire. They fought for Zamorak in the god wars.
Lord among pyrefiends. Their flames are said to scorch all who challenge it.
A demon made of demonic energy and water. If frozen, they turn into Icefiends.
Ruler of Waterfiends. They can expel water at very harmful speeds.
A demon made of ice. Killing one sometimes cools down food to pleasant temperatures.
Leader of icefiends. No heat is ever seen in the vicinity of a Icelord.
A baby phoenix. A wonder unthought of for many millennia. It loves attention.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A bird born of fire, if it dies it would simply return from its ashes.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A turnip so dastardly evil, not even demons dare to go near it. It gives the Evil chicken a run for its title.
A cute and innocent creature that would never harm you, spy on you, or find your deepest, darkest secrets.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A yak that can hardly growl 'baroo'. With long locks of hair, they eat any grass they come across.
Making their home in the islands of Neitiznot, their fur and hide are used to make clothes.
A companion to any and all adventurers, the pack yaks will not stop at any weight to bring gear to their summoner.
A Yak said to be holy and sacred. It's presence is an omen of good.
It carries a hefty amount of clue scrolls, but without any interest in reading them. Not that it has the ability to.
The smallest of all cockatrices. They may not even be able to petrify a human.
Born of a rooster and snake, these monsters lay eggs to increase their numbers.
A green egg corrupted to become a guthatrice. Their view on balance is rocky at best.
A red egg corrupted to become a Zamatrice. They petrify any who defies chaos.
A blue egg corrupted to become a Saratrice. Their eyes gaze upon any who do not uphold order.
A black egg corrupted to become a corxatrice. They get really sad when they find shiny things and they turn to stone.
A vulture egg corrupted to become a Vulatrice. Hoarding the deserts for food, they often petrify their meal accidentally.
A penguin egg corrupted to become a Pengatrice. It is unknown if it sides with the K.G.P.
A chocolate monster full of anger over its state. Its gaze will turn monsters to chocolate.
A sprout that changes its appearance depending on the season.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Workers of the hive. These kalphites are not meant for combat.
Kalphites born only to fight intruders of the hive. Their poison stings any adventurer.
The personal guardians of the hive's queen, these kalphites are far bigger than regular soldiers.
Each kalphite hive needs a queen. And upon reaching a point in their life, they change form to become better at combat.
A corrupted kalphite that has become warped. Capable of things a regular kalphite king would never be able to do.
A dragon made of runic energy. They are known to sometimes steal adventurers runes as snacks.
Unchosen by the people, they live only to claim revenge on their hated enemy. Refuses to rest until their blade tastes blood.
A mushroom hailing from Zanaris, the moon of Gielinor.
A spawn from the abyssal realm. While young, they are very aggressive.
A minion to the hive mind of the abyssal pathways. They wander the abyss in search of intruders.
A demon from the abyssal realm. They are said to manipulate the fabric of space to teleport.
An abyssal demon of phenomenal power. It acts as if the gateway to the abyss goes through its body.
A parasite from the abyss. They cling to their host; sucking them dry of energy.
Gets their name from lurking the abyss. In Gielinor, they simply follow their summoners.
A titan from the abyss summoned by a summoning obelisk. It's unclear if it enjoys to serve others.
Smallest of the wild beings of the tzhaar volcano. They fly around in the fight caves.
A fighter of the fight cave, they were originally builders of the elder god Fuh.
They fire deadly spines out of their arms, projected by their own heat.
A plague upon the tzhaar volcano. These monsters are hunted for their meat but are hard to catch.
A strong monster from the fight caves capable of firing great balls of fire from their bodies.
It's unknown for what reason, but these monsters seem to heal stronger monsters of the Tzhaar.
Possessing great strength they are a threat to any challenger of the fight caves. They struggle with small spaces.
A small creature that loves exploring what lies beyond the tzhaar volcano.
A monster and king of the fight caves. Warriors who beat one are presented with a fire cape.
Often referred to as "Nibblers". They are at the bottom of the food chain in the Inferno.
Ancestor of the Tz-Kih. They fly around in the Inferno.
Superior variant of the Tz-Kek. They are slow and powerful.
A monster found in the Inferno. They possess extremely powerful claws that let them claw at their opponents.
Superior variant of the Ket-Zek. They hurl large, projectile fire balls at their enemies. They are also capable of reviving their allies.
Superior variant of the TzTok-Jad. Opposed to being leaders in their own right, they become guardians of the imprisoned leader TzKal-Zuk.
A dangerous entity that got imprisoned deep below the TzHaar City during the ancient times. Sacrifices are regularly send to keep it at bay.
With huge self-doubts, they fear that they might be truly ugly. Its parents are unaware.
Possessing teeth infused with infernal energy and a scream that makes any grown man scared, these demons attack any who oppose them.
Waddling along playfully through the falador park. Some say they can grow to enormous sizes.
The biggest duck on Gielinor. At some point they will go on a holy pilgrimage to the far off land of Feldip.
A duck that climbed on top of a cart and has since never moved. It is now the king of the minecart.
Small and weak, they attack back with poison to any who harm them.
A pest to any resort owners. These monsters make great pets for hunters.
Having just grown big enough to move, these monsters are ready to eat anything.
A monster that is the sworn enemy of the Fremmenik. They hail from waterbirth island.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
The kings of the Dagannoth, each possessing great strength above any normal Dagannoth. They serve their queen.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
An elemental of pure chaotic energy. Its powers and behaviour is unpredictable to any enemy or friend alike.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Hatched from a brown egg, this little bird seeks only conflict.
If there are peaceful times, this bird will fly to great lengths to find a war to fight in.
Used by bandosian warlords as weapons, their claws have felled many soldiers on the battlefield.
Hatched from a purple egg, its motivations and goal is a mystery.
It closes its eyes and remains in solitude. Some say their presence is empty.
Possessing dark powers unheard of, these ravens appear at the darkest of times to watch over the world.
Hatched from a cyan egg, these birds shine in pure light.
Peacefully jittering along, they love to sing in harmonic tunes.
While not a great flier, they refract light in a great many directions due to their crystals.
Unable to move, the frogspawn patiently wait for their bodies to grow.
Denizen of any pond or lake, the frog will ribbit in the face of any foe.
A frog grown to large size. They are hunted by the Dorgeshuun for food.
A royal member cursed to become a frog. Only a kiss from an adventurer could ever save them.
A frog infused with swamp gas. They are not very mobile and are easy prey for Chompies.
A very gassy toad that has no ability to move. Only being held down by the rock its tied to. They hate their lives.
A summoned monster from the spirit realm. They get their name from the sound they make when attacking.
An abomination made by the Homunculi. Part frog part eel, it does not comprehend its existence.
While small, these spiders are used by inexperienced mages for training.
Capable of growing quite big, these spiders are usually not a threat to seasoned adventurers.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Sporting the name 'deadly red spider', these spiders protect their eggs from hoarders.
They lurk the ruins of Daemonheim. But it is most known for posessing a hood that makes you invisible.
Spider that is blessed by the son of Zamorak, Iban. They are led by their brood Kalrag.
Since they live in the jungle, they have a green coloration. This makes them invisible to see on maps.
It's body is made of ice, making it one of very few cold-blooded insects.
A really scary spider who loves webbing houses for the spider queen. Not doing so is an offense and will leave a spider in your bathtub.
It is customary for the lord of Death, Harold, to always have cobwebs in his house. If not, this spider will punish him.
Staring eerily at anyone with its many eyes. It is unsure if its life was a folly or a mistake.
Crawlers who search for food all day. They once became famous due to a combat expert.
A far larger cave crawler who might venture deeper into caves than their younger counterparts.
The apex of the cave crawlers. Their bodies are so solid, moss and plants have begun growing on them.
Small tortoises bred by the grand tree for use as mounts. They love cabbage.
These large creatures are usually ridden by 3 gnome warriors, each using a different combat style.
Tortoise warped by Aposandra but the experiment failed. They now lurk the poison waste sewers.
A summonable tortoise that loves to carry items. Its offense is pitiable however.
A guardian of Guthix sent to fend off the void invasion. It can finish off a pest queen easily.
These sea turtles sometimes get caught by fishing trawlers. Therefore, they are hard to catch in bulk.
A slime that seemingly absorbs nutrients as it goes. It's unclear if they possess a will.
A gelatinous blob of slime, what is inside it is seemingly skeletons and organs. It is unknown where they came from.
A jelly so warped it could never be served to anyone. It's insides are beyond comprehension.
Even in the spirit realm there exists jellies. Eating humans will cause them indigestion.
A green swamp lizard usually found in Morytania. They love Guam leaves.
Apparently related to desert lizards. They can fire a fiery breath at their enemies.
Usually found around lava, these Salamanders have a fondness for herbs.
Found only in the wilderness, these salamanders are rarely hunted due to the dangers of the Wilderness.
As a strike against the gods, a black lizard became augmented by the inventions of mankind. Now stronger than ever, it strikes back.
As they have no eyelids they lick their eyes to make sure they don't dry up.
Capable of looking in any direction, shooting its tongue like an arrow, and colour-changing skin. This lizard has everything.
One of the lower forms of Chtonian demons. They hunger for blood their entire lives.
Often used as pets for Vampyres, these monsters will salivate upon even small whiffs of blood.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A bloodveld experimented upon to truly understand hemomancy. The experiments failed.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Hatched from a pink egg. These birds seek to uphold law.
Flying swiftly through the sky, these birds will fly to kingdoms that uphold the law.
Hailing from the homeworld of the aviansies, they possess wings able to carry them anywhere.
Hatched from a regular egg, this bird needs a god to align with.
Knowing that following a god is a folly, they want to prove to everyone that gods are of no use to them.
Fighting with no aid from the gods, the godless assume they are the true believers of Guthix.
Born of an orange egg, this bird holds a small orb in honor of Tumeken.
Balancing atop its orb, it will stand still even in the biggest of desert storms.
Balancing the orb along its tail feathers, it is said to only drop it if it has no strength left to fight.
As they refuse to help you see in the dark, their only use is as a makeshift weapon.
Running great lengths at surprisingly fast paces, only seasoned hunters seem able to catch them.
Expelling fire from their husks, they seem to smell like bonfires. It's hard to let them out in the wild as they start forest fires.
A very skittish creature that when agitated, will simply roll away. Sometimes it rolls down hills and gets mad it has to walk up the hill again.
A airut commander under the god of Tuska. They seek nothing but destruction.
A spirit guardian who fell victim to airut shamans. It now summons jellyfish to fight for it.
A guardian spirit who holds the key to the anima mundi of its world. It feels shackled to the body it has.
A fat bird that has trouble flying. Ogres hunt them for food.
A bird so fat that it could feed an Ogre for an entire week. The trick to catching them is a secret.
Trained as mounts by the gnomes, these birds have no quarrel with fighting any who challenge them.
Failed attempts to make the terrorbird smarter warped it to become like this. It is a failure.
A terrorbird from the spirit realm. They can carry a great load of baggage on their backs.
Created by the homunculus, their reserves of meat and fat are so large, that it could feed a family of 3 on lobster for a week.
A young wolf who prefers to stay inside caves. Their favourite treat is cave mice.
They form packs and hunt together in a flock. This way, survival becomes easier for the pack as they collaborate.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A big and dangerous wolf from Arendar gates. They sometimes come down to Isafdar to hunt the unknowing.
A big wolf said in the Fremennik Tales to be a wolf capable of even swallowing the sun.
A big wolf said in the Fremennik Tales to be the harbinger of Ragnarok, the events that end the world.
A crafty and shrewd vulpine. Known for sneaking into chicken pens to steal food.
A fox that has lived so long it grew additional tails. Each tail gave it more power.
A wolf from the spirit world. Its howl can scare and repel any enemy, making it a good companion for new adventurers.
Sorcerer of the Cywir clan, it fights in the name of Seren with the power of the spirit realm.
A delight for people who chop down trees. These nests often have small eggs in them.
Mostly harmless birds that enjoy looking down on people from coathangers in a scornful way.
Often seen with the Freaky Forester. These birds serve no purpose except being food.
It's wings are not ready to fly, yet it hunts for goatweed all day.
Known by a local farmer as "big bird". It has large wings capable of knocking farmers over.
A young unicorn pure of will and naive to the dangers of the world.
With a pure mind, the unicorn is said to grant blessings. They enjoy the company of virgins and pure souls.
A stallion from the spirit realm. With great healing powers, they help their allies in battles.
Native to Isafdar, these small critters love the taste of papaya, which are in short supply in the elven lands.
Hunters to the core. They prey on Pawya. If threatened, they will curl up into a defensive mode. Their spikes are used for potions.
A young bear with much to learn. Easily tricked by honey. Tends to repay favours with an oblivious slap.
A large monster of the ursa family. They will eat large amounts of food before hibernating in the winter.
A god of the mountain. A cannibal posed as the Kendall once and ate whoever came close to his domain.
A bear native to Archeron. They held penguins as slaves and are the sworn enemies of the seals.
A very curious bear from the spirit realm. They will seemingly entertain any audience in an informative way.
A big horned monster from the Karamja jungles. Their horns are so solid, they will leave a dent on even steel.
A graahk from the spirit realm. They are not as easily teased as their Gielinorian counterpart.
A devil that makes a sound so dastardly any dog will bark at it in fear. It cleans up its domain however.
Expelling great amounts of smoke, it is hard to know if it does so to defend itself, or annoy its opponents.
A monster said to be so unstable it could blow up at any moment. Yet it keeps on living as if nothing is a threat.
A monster who will make even a grown man choke on his own breath. Any who challenge it should wear a facemask.
Said to be a danger to itself and any around it. It will refuse to do anything but harm those it loves.
A newly hatched dragon. When they eat, they sometimes burn their food and become grumpy.
A small dragon. Dragons were originally made by the dragonkin to relieve them of their curse.
Sporting incredibly thick hide, dragons are killed for their bones and hide which sells for a good price.
Scarred from battle, these dragon's are battle hardened and stronger than the regular kind.
Small and cute, they have yet to breathe fire. They are still killed anyway.
A weaker dragon that can still pack a punch. Adventurers choose to kill them for trade.
A dragon that should never be underestimated. Aside from being coloured blue, they are distinguished by spiky horns.
A young creature secluded to the Brimhaven Dungeon. They make friends with dogs.
A strong creature hidden away in inconvenient locations. They are not valued as high as their cousins.
A dragon that should never be underestimated. Aside from being coloured red, they are distinguished by a pointy horn.
The elite of all baby dragon forms. They tend to stick close to their parents.
All hail the feared black dragon. They were once believed to be the strongest monsters of all.
A dragon that should never be underestimated. Aside from being coloured black, they are distinguished by curvy horns.
A monster that should no longer exist. Finding one is a statistical anomaly.
Slayer of Crandor Island. Elvarg is a threat to be reckoned with for any unprepared adventurer.
A 3-headed black dragon made by Kerapac. Its real name is Shakorexis.
The first dragon ever created, laid to slumber as it serves to use anymore. Grotworms have since infested it.
A really small hand. So small, it would come in handy at any kind of on-hand situation. They hate puns.
A hand from Viggora's Folly, a tower that fell into the ground due to unstable foundations. They love rings and gloves.
A crawling hand without any skin left. Some theorize there could be skeletal feet out there.
A hand so big it will crush anything it can. Despite lacking a body, it really packs a punch.
Perhaps you should avoid shaking the hand. It has been rotting for some time.
A creature so persistent, only a broad type of weapons could ever wish to harm it.
A turoth grown to prime strength. Stronger than others of its kind, it will fight till its last breath to feed itself.
Its size is far larger than other turoth's making it more dangereous. But not that much dangereous.
A turoth who, due to a number of inconvenient events and a fallout with Meg the Adventurer, now possesses a sock.
A kurask not fully grown yet. To prove its worth, it must travel to Karamja and return home with a pineapple.
Having returned from Karamja with its prized possession, it is now marked an adult and can be a respected member of its herd.
The king of its herd. They lead their herd with wisdom and experience.
It leads with a stern hand, demanding fruit as tribute for its protection.
A small monster mostly seen as prey by everyone else than other kebbits.
A monster that defends itself with camouflage in snowy areas. It does not like the cold however.
One of the more dangerous kebbits, they have massive fangs that bite predators. They are not that smart however.
Their spots confuse predators by causing optical illusions while running.
They can run at great speed without making a sound. This is due to their sleek fur.
These monsters are swift runners. Fast regular traps are no match for them. Falcons, however, easily catch them.
These kebbits have grown small spikes in an attempt to defend themselves. But they got hunted even more by humans for trade.
A kebbit that is usually hunted by intermediate hunters. They hate falcons with a passion.
These kebbits will lower their bodies to the ground and then throw their backs into their enemies for self defence.
A kebbit that has grown to an extreme size. Despite its size, it is still a weak kebbit.
They only live in the desert, despite there not being much food around.
One of the more common kebbits, hailing from the Piscatoris hunter area.
A kebbit with a barb tail so sharp, it can even be used to fish.
Being struck by disease, this kebbit awaits for it's life to end. Possibly dragging more of its kind with it.
A kebbit made entirely of chocolate, usually by the powers of a chocatrice.
Denizens of Karamja, these creatures love bananas and playing tricks on humans.
Monkey trained to prime speed and form. They defend the Ape Atoll from any outsiders.
Monkeys arisen by necromantic arts and locked away in the caves beneath the Ape Atoll.
A stronger kind of primate that are used when the speed of a monkey is not enough, and raw strength is needed.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A swift hunter from the Feldip region. Their fur is adapted to camouflage in the jungles.
A hunter from the spirit realm. These monsters have really sharp senses, making them great partners for hunters.
The apex predator of the snowy north. Their fangs are really sharp, but if they break, they cannot be regrown.
A kyatt from the spirit realm. Capable of teleporting it and its adventurer to where it pleases, when it pleases.
So small it can hide anywhere, it needs to make a decision how to survive in the future.
A crab made of solid rock. They stay along beaches motionlessly. If a rock moves, it might be a rock crab.
Far larger than it's smaller counterpart, it has become a lot harder to hide as a small rock.
A crab so ancient, fossils can be seen on it. Archaeologists want to study them but are no match to their powers.
A lobsters pretending to be a rock. Except it wasn't a rock, it was a rock lobster.
These crabs are mainly found in desert regions, using sand instead of rocks.
Mainly found in swamp's, they use whatever they can find as substitute shells.
A bigger rockcrab from Waterbirth Island. They are far larger and deadlier but prefer to stay immobile.
A lobster from the spirit realm. Smaller and swifter, these lobsters are really good at fishing underwater.
A creature that is light on its feet but are otherwise useless. Their meat is tasty and their feet bring luck to lumberjacks.
A rabbit from the spirit realm with antlers and magical powers. It also seemingly grants a great deal of camouflage to those in its herd.
A swamp creature from the spirit realm. They prefer to swallow their fish raw.
A feared monster of Morytania. It gets it name from the talons it possesses that has killed many adventurers.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
A friendly critter not to be confused with the ferret of doom. These muspelids will gladly hunt rabbits.
An automation made of clockwork to mimic a mouse. Cats love to play with these.
Toy doll made from clockwork. It pirouettes and dances whenever it can.
Made of clockwork, it seemingly follows its duty of marching to war. Even if there isn't any...
Penguin toy made of clockwork. If someone was small enough to fit, they could probably control it from the inside.
An automation made of clockwork to mimic mans best friend. They refuse to meow.
Magically infused carpets capable of flight. They are used as transportation in the Kharidian desert.
A chair that has seemingly gained life. They love to play tricks on adventurers who enter their domain.
An axe posessed by a ghost. Their movements are primitive, but deadly.
A pickaxe possessed by a long passed away miner. Even in death it keeps on chopping at anything.
Toy of a being that is now extinct. A horse is apparently something like a hornless unicorn that tasted delicious.
Marionette who dances to the puppetmaster. If there are no strings, it will fight back.
Sold due to high demand of Dragon kites. Adventurers got upset it was not a kiteshield and sales plummeted.
Armour reanimated by magic to become a test of strength. They are great for combat training.
Just a normal tree without any leaves or life left. Something like this could never move.
Born of vines and plants, these monsters are one with nature and take many forms.
A being from another plane. They are made entirely of electrical energy and will expel it at every opportunity.
Unrelated to the K.G.P. The turkeys are trying to launch an attack on humans. Humans don't care since it is thanksgiving.
Grown and ready to defend itself. It retaliates against adventurers to fight for its freedom. They are then eaten.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Tenacious to a T, they will relentlessly attack adventurers embarking into the jade vine.
Nothing Interesting Happens.
Despite the look of it, its beak is actually very brittle and prone to breaking.
Its blue colorations are meant to disguise it under the sea. This makes it easier to fight prey.
They are commonly referred to as "melee fish" since they are very physically strong.
A chunk of runestone from a rock infused by the stone of Jas.
Infused with the energy of the runic altars, the rune essence gains the powers of the altars.
In large supplies, runes are capable of creating spells. But not knowing what to do with them might expel said energy.
A small bird often found amongst docks. They tend to clean harbours of food scraps otherwise left unattended.
Pelicans lurk fishing platforms hoping to either steal a fish, or for a fishing adventurer to give them a treat.
Flying around Cairn Island, these birds fish for food.
Baron von Hattenkrapper. Sworn rival of Count Ludvig Koppenploppen. Known as the slayer of barrelchests on Bloodsplatter island.
Count Ludwig Koppenploppen. Sworn rival to Baron von Hattenkrapper. Known to have eaten many meals on The rock.
Flightless, the bird has nothing but it's own name that holds any value. It fights with all it has.
Fishers with good summoning levels summon these birds to improve their catches.
A smaller, limbless kind of dragon that prefers to sail along the desert. The sandstorms cannot damage them.
A bigger, limbless dragon. While it has no fire breath, it is still a threat to unprepared adventurers.
Their bodies are covered in slime, no one but other ghosts would dare to hug it.
Found in the jungles of Karamja, these snakes are usually harmless to most travelers.
Their necks can enlargen to scare their enemies. They dance when they are charmed by a flute.
A cobra from the spirit realm. They can corrupt eggs, making them into cockatrice egg's
Guardian of Guthix, this snake was set to guard the residual sadness of Guthix left in the rocks of lumbridge.
Found deep beneath Misthalin and Etceteria, these snakes only live in underwater caves.
Grown to a size far larger than any other snake, it preys on what enters its caves.
The meaning of Cupholders is still unknown.
Created by betraying a friend and turning them into a polishing rock for the purpose of completing a quest.
The Elder Gods created several Elder Artefacts. The Pillar was not one of them. Despite this, it killed Mother Mallum in one attack.
A troll delicacy made by mixing a pet rock into a soup of cabbage. You can really taste the rock in it.
Most Slagilith are caused by unknowing adventurers animating the face of a rock. It becomes sentient and will try to kill them.
These rocks are known to sneak into a player's inventory when they are least needed.
These golden rocks are known to sneak into a player's inventory when they are sometimes needed.
They dance with the fury of a mighty statue. Having one at a party is sure to raise the roof.
When a yak dies, that is usually it. Unless they become zombie yaks.
A yak tasked with the important duty of bearing the food supply for an entire winter, without eating it.
Dairy cows are specialized in producing the highest quality milk and can be milked by any passing adventurers.
Strawberry cows come to be by feeding a dairy cow plenty of strawberries throughout its period of growth.
It is said that if you shake a vanilla cow enough and use a bucket on it, it will create a milkshake.
According to several surveys, 80% of players prefer the Chocolate cow over the vanilla or strawberry ones.
A cow posessing the rare qualities of its fellow cows. When slaughtered, the pink parts are usually left behind.
When a slayer comes near, the matriarch will challenge it to a battle so epic, only cowhide is left.
The cows of Sophanem and Menaphos were cursed by the devourer, and are thus slowly awaiting death.
The apex of bulls. They are capable of knocking players over, and filling their stomachs for a slayer task.
Far smarter than regular cows or bulls, they reside in the Stronghold of Security for no apparent reason.
Whenever they see humans with horny helmets, they will ruthlessly charge at them for a duel.
Fred the farmer collects balls of wool in order to create the ultimate cow. The trojan cow.
A chicken without any clear purpose or meaning. The real mystery is why it exists.
The horse of Frank, the fifth member of the clan, "The Horsemen".
The Scientist Avalani sent several chicken into the sky to research the clan citadel. Not many returned.
The fusion of 4 different chickens sent to certain death. Its power is that of 4 whole chickens.
Serving as the steed of Frank, the fifth member of The Horsemen. This chicken has done nothing worth mentioning.
Golden rams tend to be monopolised by the troll Lalli. But their wool can be used to create enchanted lyres.
Known for eating mostly anything, these goats are great for controlling grasslands on the mountain.
As they wander the desert near Nardah they sometimes find adventurers killing them for their horns.
Sheep born with black fur are worth less than white ones because their wool can not be coloured.
Their hooves are so expertly crafted, they can climb even the steepes mountain. Despite this, they are often used for soup.
Despite being found in another plane of existence, some made it to Gielinor to fight by Zamorak's side during the God Wars.
A sheep coloured to pretend there was a plague in Kandarin. This was instigated by the faction of mourners.
Made by Dr. Fenkenstrain, these experiments are either sheep in wolf clothing, or the opposite.
A perfectly normal sheep. In no way is it collecting information about you to use against you.
Their pincers are designed to hold on to their enemies. But at this stage, they are too small to effectively use them.
Once a year, crabs come out of their shell to grow bigger, but they are vulnerable while doing so.
Capable of dealing massive damage, these crabs use their mighty pincers to battle.
A delicious, cute, and sweet crab found in the deep ruins of Daemonheim.
These crabs are mostly herded by Mogres; ogres living underwater. Their meat is a delicacy.
A crab pumped full of rum under the orders of Rabbid Jack. They are served as a delicacy in Menaphos.
When adventurers Marmaros and Thok explored Daemonheim, these crabs would snip their fishing nets.
Easily recognized by their blue shell, these crabs linger in the deep caverns of Daemonheim.
Crabs that are so elusive and rare that even expert fishermen have trouble fishing them. Or live long enough to return to the bank with them.
By giving a crab a knife, it is said their attack power triples. They are a threat to behold as they dance.
A small crab more known for what they carry on their back. Which can vary in a lot of ways.
A lobster so rare they are mostly found in player-owned homes. They are easily recognized by their blue shell.
Found near the shores of Daemonheim, these lobsters are quite big, but otherwise harmless to all.
A rare and elusive lobster. Fabled as an unbelievably rare creature, people are willing to pay 100k for one. Limited time offer.
Known for their mottled texture, these eels tends to be fished with the aid of falconry.
Everything but appetizing, these eels are known for their many short fins.
For unknown reasons these eels seem to have some lesser holy qualities to them.
Eels that enjoy lurking in the darkest of waters as to not be caught. When caught, they are anything but pretty.
The biggest of all water-dwelling monsters of Daemonheim. The Cave Moray is a meal in itself for adventurers.
A fish so vile, no one would ever attempt to eat one. Except maybe Thok.
The meaning of Cupholders is still unknown.
